Package: kmod-keys-encrypted
Version: 6.6.50-r1
Depends: kernel (=6.6.50~6df682083a13b90755cc110536a6646d-r1), kmod-crypto-cbc, kmod-crypto-hmac, kmod-crypto-rng, kmod-crypto-sha256, kmod-keys-trusted
Source: feeds/base/kernel/linux
SourceName: kernel
License: GPL-2.0-only
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Section: kernel
SourceDateEpoch: 1726129854
Architecture: aarch64_cortex-a53
Installed-Size: 30720
Filename: kmod-keys-encrypted_6.6.50-r1_aarch64_cortex-a53.ipk
Size: 8781
SHA256sum: 7f7bf48cd259a4cbd2ba6665c628c38db97edb8f4aa1b659f81b20b22bc346f9
Description:  This module provides support for create/encrypting/decrypting keys
 in the kernel.  Encrypted keys are kernel generated random numbers,
 which are encrypted/decrypted with a 'master' symmetric key. The
 'master' key can be either a trusted-key or user-key type.
 Userspace only ever sees/stores encrypted blobs.

Package: kmod-keys-trusted
Version: 6.6.50-r1
Depends: kernel (=6.6.50~6df682083a13b90755cc110536a6646d-r1), kmod-crypto-hash, kmod-crypto-hmac, kmod-crypto-sha1, kmod-tpm
Source: feeds/base/kernel/linux
SourceName: kernel
